Gbenga Odogun,Lokoja The Department of Petroleum Resources on Tuesday  sealed off two filling stations in Kogi State for allegedly short-changing their customers. The body also closed  a gas station for operating without a licence. The  state DPR Operation Controller,    Amos Jokodola, who led  the  team, told reporters in  Lokoja that  they decided to seal  Emmalis and Always filling stations in the city because they were not treating their customers well. Jokodola warned petroleum dealers in the state to desist from under-dispensing of petroleum products. He said,  “We are preparing for  Christmas and New Year. We  will monitor the distribution and the selling of petrol, kerosine and gas to customers during and after the Yelutide season.” Jokodola  advised petroleum product consumers not to indulge in panic buying, saying  there was  petrol, kerosine and gas that could  last till February 2020. CopyrightPUNCH.
